&lt;p&gt;(i.e.,) are looking for a Client Partner to take ownership of one of our most significant client relationships. This is a senior client-facing role for someone who&#39;s as comfortable managing an executive stakeholder as they are untangling a delivery problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research indicates that certain demographic groups, such as women, may be less inclined to apply for a role unless they meet all the job requirements. If you&#39;re interested in this role, we strongly encourage you to apply, as you might be just what we&#39;re looking for.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll become the primary day-to-day leader for a major enterprise account, owning a complex portfolio of digital and technology work. This isn&#39;t a project manager role. It&#39;s a senior position for someone who can sit in front of a client and say, &quot;I understand the problem. Leave it with me, I&#39;ll come back with a solution&quot; and mean it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll manage the relationship, lead multiple streams of work, spot commercial opportunities, and keep delivery teams coordinated and accountable, all while protecting account health and growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll sit within a cross-functional team to support with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing executive and senior stakeholder relationships across a large, complex account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading multiple concurrent streams of work, from enterprise websites and platform delivery to integrations and digital transformation programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying commercial opportunities and resolving client challenges before they escalate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinating delivery teams and translating between client needs and delivery reality without creating unnecessary escalation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building deep trust with client stakeholders over time, becoming an integral part of the account&#39;s future growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who genuinely enjoys spending time with clients, who&#39;s curious about people, organisations and industries, and who builds trust naturally rather than transactionally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More specifically, you&#39;ll bring:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record leading large, complex client accounts with multiple concurrent workstreams, ideally from an agency or digital, technology or consulting environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial instincts, with the judgement to protect long-term account health while identifying growth opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enough technical credibility in websites, digital platforms, CMS ecosystems, APIs and integrations to have confident, credible conversations with both clients and delivery teams. You don&#39;t need to be the deepest technical expert in the room&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High emotional intelligence: you&#39;re patient, adaptable, calm under pressure, and politically aware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort operating within large, hierarchical, relationship-driven enterprise environments, where issues are often resolved through management layers rather than direct confrontation, and where sensing an unspoken concern matters as much as hearing a spoken one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine point of view on how AI is changing consulting, delivery and client relationships not just familiarity with using it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
