&lt;p&gt;(i.e.,) are looking for a Strategy Consultant, Labs (AI and Frontier Tech) to join the Labs Growth team and lead client engagements at the frontier of AI and emerging technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a role for someone who thrives in ambiguity — someone who can shape a problem, run an experiment, and bring a cross-functional team along for the ride.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research indicates that certain demographic groups, such as women, may be less inclined to apply for a role unless they meet all the job requirements. If you&#39;re interested in this role, we strongly encourage you to apply, as you might be just what we&#39;re looking for.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Strategy Consultant in our Labs Growth team, you’ll work directly with clients to explore what’s possible with Generative and Agentic AI, and turn those possibilities into real propositions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll lead engagements end-to-end: from framing the problem and running experiments, through to developing propositions and handing validated opportunities over to the Studio team for scaled delivery. Reporting to the Director, Commercial and Growth (Labs), you’ll shape the Labs commercial pipeline and help build the practice as it grows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Day-to-day, you’ll be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shaping client proposals, pitches, and engagements, and contributing to the Labs commercial pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying industry and client opportunities, and developing propositions that apply agentic solutions and frontier technology — including hands-on experimentation with new tools and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading cross-functional Labs teams of service designers, data, and technical SMEs through engagements that are often ambiguous in scope, audience, or outcome.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applying creative and systems thinking to help clients architect future-ready businesses and products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with the Studio team to hand over validated opportunities for scaled delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping build and evolve the Labs capability, including our methods, assets, and service offering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value demonstrated experience across two or more of the following areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading work in ambiguity - you’re comfortable navigating undefined problems and shifting requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-framing capability, including writing clear problem statements and assessing opportunities through desirability, viability, and feasibility lenses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running experimental initiatives from concept through to pilot, with a clear point of view on when to iterate, pivot, or stop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience applying AI tools, with working knowledge of Agentic AI across domains like commerce, engineering, and product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitating design thinking workshops, with the ability to apply systems thinking to complex client challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with service and experience design principles, an understanding of relevant technology considerations, and the ability to build business cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of governance, data privacy, and secure-environment considerations relevant to AI and experimental technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing high-quality presentations and presenting to leadership and executive audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
